ed a bachelors degree from the university of delawarecitation needed entertainment careeredit probst worked for johnson  johnson and clorox before being recruited into the video game industry through activision in  two years later he joined ea as vice president for sales until  he then took on the role of the companys senior vice president of the publishing division from  he was promoted to president of electronic arts in  remaining in that position until  during this time he was also pronounced ceo of electronic arts in  which he held onto until april  next generation named his one of the  most important people in the games industry of  remarking that probst may not be as colorful a character as his predecessor  trip hawkins but he does seem adept at combining the freedom and daring of creativity with the restraints and common sense of a commercial operation when president and chief operating officer john riccitiello resigned in april  probst became his successor riccitiello was rehired as ceo in  he retained his nonoperational duties as chairman he then worked as executive chairman of electronic arts inc from march   to january   and former chief executive officer of the companycitation needed according to eas  annual report probst is the biggest individual shareholder in ea owning  shares and the right to acquire a further  million which combined accounts for  percent of the company probst sits on the boards of two cancer research groups the v foundation and abc in addition to his work at electronic arts probst also served as the chairman of digital entertainment corporation of america olympic careeredit in  he was made the us olympic committee chairman of the board five years after his appointment as chairman of the usoc probst was elected as an ioc member at the th ioc session in buenos aires in september  probst worked with many other ioc groups as well probst has served on the ioc international relations and the ioc radio and television commissions he assumed the position of chair of the ioc press commission in citation needed referencesedit  lawrence francis probst iii  personal appointments free information from companies house betacompanieshousegovuk retrieved    grubb jeffrey ea sports chief andrew wilson is electronic arts’ new ceo venturebeat retrieved september     longtime exec larry probst to leave ea but remain on its board gamasutracom  retrieved       power players next generation imagine media   november          larry probst  usoc board of directors teamusaorg retrieved    ioc session elects nine new members  olympic news olympicorg  retrieved   external linksedit ea company bios larry probst john riccitiello resigns as ea president article from cnnmoney electronic arts  on the record larry probst from sfgatecom v t e presidents of the united states olympic committee albert spalding – david r francis – caspar whitney – frederic b pratt – robert m thompson – gustavus t kirby – robert m thompson – william c prout – henry g lapham interim  douglas macarthur – avery brundage – tug wilson – doug roby – franklin orth – clifford h buck interim  elected – philip krumm – robert kane – william e simon – john b kelly jr  robert h helmick interim  elected – bill hybl interim – leroy t walker – bill hybl – sandra baldwin – marty mankamyer interim  elected – william c martin interim – peter ueberroth – larry probst –present retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlelarryprobstoldid categories  birthsliving peopleamerican chairmen of corporationsamerican technology chief executivesuniversity of delaware alumnielectronic arts employeesinternational olympic committee membersjohnson  johnson peoplebusinesspeople from delawarevideo game businesspeoplehidden categories articles with hcardsall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from march  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more s